Parents and pupils are hoping that the lost years of schooling can somehow be regained. Manqoba Mchunu has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Parents and pupils are hoping that the lost years of schooling can somehow be regained. Many have welcomed the Basic Education Minister's decision to have schools return to full capacity. READ: Back to school | Full-time classes resume But there are still concerns. Student union COSAS says it welcomes the decision for schools to return to normal, but it will be keeping a close eye on how things unfold. * eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports.